WebdriverIO + Mocha is the best choice for a solid Appium setup. We’ll build a real automation framework with:

✅ WebdriverIO (test runner & driver)

✅ Mocha (test engine)

✅ Appium service (mobile support)

✅ Allure Reporter (reports)

✅ Page Object structure

🔧 Step 1: Initialize package.json

(If not done yet)

npm init -y

📦 Step 2: Install Core Dependencies

Run this in your project directory:

npm install --save-dev \
    @wdio/cli \
    @wdio/local-runner \
    @wdio/mocha-framework \
    @wdio/allure-reporter \
    @wdio/appium-service \
    appium

🚗 Step 3: Install Appium Drivers

iOS & Android drivers must be installed inside Appium, not npm:

npx appium driver install xcuitest
npx appium driver install uiautomator2

⚙️ Step 4: Run WDIO Configuration Wizard

This will create wdio.conf.js

npx wdio config


🧭 In Wizard — choose:

Question	Select
Test runner	local
Framework	mocha
Spec files location	./tests/**/*.spec.js
Reporter	allure
Plugins	Appium Service (@wdio/appium-service)
Base URL	leave blank ("")
Generate page objects?	Yes (optional)
Install dependencies	No (we already did)
📁 After Setup — Folder Structure
mobile-automation/
 ├─ wdio.conf.js
 ├─ package.json
 ├─ /tests
 ├─ /pages
 ├─ /reports (after running)

🟢 Next Step – First Mobile Test

